'''''The Wraith''''' is a live television comedy play presented on Australian television in 1957. Broadcast on [[ABC1|ABC]], it was originally telecast in Sydney, and shown in Melbourne via a [[kinescope]] recording.<ref name="age">{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=DVURAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ppUDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6079%2C3311600|newspaper=The Age|date=23 May 1957|title=Mystery-Comedy on Kinescope|page=12}}</ref>

Duration was 30 minutes, in black and white. It was written by W. Graeme-Holder, and had previously been presented on radio during the 1930s. It is not known if the kinescope recording of the television version is still extant.

==Premise==
The film is a comedy about a mysterious burglar.

==Cast==
*Leonard Bullen - Burglar
*Normal Cull - Burglar
*Joan Lord - Lady

==Production==
The play was based on a 1936 radio play that was often performed in the late 1930s.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article36379104 |title=POLL RESULTS OVER AIR |newspaper=[[The Advertiser (Adelaide)]] |location=South Australia |date=16 October 1937 |accessdate=18 February 2019 |page=21 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article36380220 |title=5CLâ€”411 Metres |newspaper=[[The Advertiser (Adelaide)]] |location=South Australia |date=20 October 1937 |accessdate=18 February 2019 |page=20 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>

